# Seer — Agent Lifecycle Service:
    ## P0 (Blocking):
        [ ] SEER-ALS-001: Training Spec CRD schema not finalized — cannot create Training Spec
        [ ] SEER-ALS-002: Employment Spec CRD schema not finalized — cannot create Employment Spec
        [ ] SEER-ALS-003: Raw Agent deployment model (containers, serverless) needs specification
        [ ] SEER-ALS-004: Agent registration and lifecycle API needs specification
    ## P1 (High):
        [ ] SEER-ALS-005: Guardrail definition format and enforcement mechanism needs specification
        [ ] SEER-ALS-006: Authority enforcement at runtime — how Seer enforces delegation limits

# Seer — Context Assembly Engine:
    ## P0 (Blocking):
        [ ] SEER-CAE-001: Context Assembly Engine APIs (compile context, retrieval adapters, ranking, truncation, provenance) — currently placeholder
    ## P1 (High):
        [ ] SEER-CAE-003: SDK/API for retrieving from Hub Memory Services
    ## P2 (Medium):
        [ ] SEER-CAE-002: Token budgeting algorithms for large context windows

# Seer — Runtime & Deployment:
    ## P0 (Blocking):
        [ ] SEER-RTD-001: Seer runtime infrastructure details incomplete — cannot deploy agent
    ## P1 (High):
        [ ] SEER-RTD-002: Container deployment specification for Seer runtime
        [ ] SEER-RTD-003: Model Gateway integration (model routing, failover) — documented but incomplete

# Seer — Agent Observability:
    ## P2 (Medium):
        [ ] SEER-OBS-001: Seer observability SDK specification incomplete
        [ ] SEER-OBS-002: Integration with Olympus Watch needs clarification

# Seer — Agent Evaluation:
    ## P2 (Medium):
        [ ] SEER-EVL-001: Agent Evaluation Service API specification incomplete
        [ ] SEER-EVL-002: CI/CD integration for agent testing — quality gates
        [ ] SEER-EVL-003: Sandbox environment provisioning — how sandbox is created
        [ ] SEER-EVL-004: Deterministic replay harness — replay decisions using stored evidence


=======================================================
********* HUB *********
=======================================================

# Hub — Cognitive Audit Fabric (CAF):
    ## P0 (Blocking):
        [x] HUB-CAF-001: CAF schema specification (DecisionRecord, EvidenceBundle, etc.) — DONE: All 8 record types defined with schemas
    ## P1 (High):
        [x] HUB-CAF-002: CAF-to-Memory-Store Contract — DONE: memory-store-contract.md (CRD registration, HTTPS retrieval, JWS auth, views)
        [ ] HUB-CAF-003: CAF Memory Store Catalog — registry of stores, capabilities, routing logic
        [ ] HUB-CAF-004: CAF Explainer Services — explanation generation APIs, audience formatting, counterfactual generation
        [ ] HUB-CAF-005: Context snapshot storage and ID lifecycle — where stored, how referenced
    ## P2 (Medium):
        [ ] HUB-CAF-006: CAF Record Content Schema Repository — central registry (olympus://schemas/...), versioning, validation
        [ ] HUB-CAF-007: Context hashing for replay — reproducibility
        [ ] HUB-CAF-008: Legal holds representation and enforcement
        [ ] HUB-CAF-009: CAF as control plane for Knowledge Bank (not just Memory) — should CAF govern Knowledge?
        [ ] HUB-CAF-010: CAF explicit implementation of AOSM OPD requirements (Observability, Predictability, Directability)
    ## Completed:
        [x] Record relationships and traversal patterns — DONE: record-relationships.md
        [x] UUID convention for all IDs — DONE: documented in all schemas
        [x] case_id universal binding — DONE: all records navigable from case_id
        [x] hub_metadata optional section — DONE: all records have Hub context fields
        [x] Typed content convention with MIME types — DONE: content_type for structured fields
        [x] Human-readable serialization requirement (JSON default) — DONE: documented in README

# Hub — Memory Services:
    ## P1 (High):
        [ ] HUB-MEM-001: Memory Services query API specification — cannot retrieve precedent
        [ ] HUB-MEM-002: Memory indexing and search (semantic + filter) implementation details
        [ ] HUB-MEM-003: Retention and deletion semantics (PII, legal hold) — compliance risk
        [ ] HUB-MEM-004: PII classification + redaction strategy for fraud data — no classifier pipeline
        [ ] HUB-MEM-005: Agent Memory SDK/API and authentication/authorization
    ## P2 (Medium):
        [ ] HUB-MEM-006: Promotion criteria and workflow (agent → enterprise memory) — who approves, what thresholds
        [ ] HUB-MEM-007: Unified ESPP taxonomy across Enterprise Memory — Enterprise uses different types than Agent
        [ ] HUB-MEM-008: HandoffContext schema and task management UI/UX integration
        [ ] HUB-MEM-009: Semantic Memory Store contract — entity, fact, relationship record types
        [ ] HUB-MEM-010: Procedural Memory Store contract — skill, pattern record types
        [ ] HUB-MEM-011: Preference Memory Store contract — user/agent preference record types
        [ ] HUB-MEM-012: Hypothesis promotion workflow — episodic → semantic/procedural

# Hub — Knowledge Services / Knowledge Bank:
    ## P1 (High):
        [ ] HUB-KNW-001: Knowledge Bank ingress pipelines, chunking strategies, retrieval algorithms — RAG setup unclear
        [ ] HUB-KNW-002: Knowledge Bank retrieval API specification — cannot retrieve policy
    ## P2 (Medium):
        [ ] HUB-KNW-003: Chunking and embedding strategies for policy documents
        [ ] HUB-KNW-004: Provenance tracking for retrieved chunks — source tracking for RAG
        [ ] HUB-KNW-005: Policy versioning and approval workflow integration
        [ ] HUB-KNW-006: CLI/API/CRD for Knowledge Bank creation and document ingestion — subsystem marked stub
        [ ] HUB-KNW-007: Knowledge base reference integration with Seer Training Spec
    ## P3 (Low):
        [ ] HUB-KNW-008: Structured policy/rules vs docs in Knowledge Bank distinction

# Hub — Tool Registry / Direct Tool Dispatcher:
    ## P1 (High):
        [ ] HUB-TLS-001: Human-in-the-loop checkpoint implementation for high-impact actions — approval flow unclear
    ## P2 (Medium):
        [ ] HUB-TLS-002: Canonical tool registration flow and runtime invocation contract
        [ ] HUB-TLS-003: Approval workflows (task system hooks, queue routing) for high-risk actions

# Hub — Scenario Management / Hub-Seer Integration:
    ## P0 (Blocking):
        [ ] HUB-SCN-001: Seer agent binding in Hub Automation Spec — how Hub invokes Seer agents
    ## P1 (High):
        [ ] HUB-SCN-002: Runtime selection (Seer vs other Hub runtimes) — when to use which
        [ ] HUB-SCN-003: AI delegation to Seer agents — task handoff mechanism
        [ ] HUB-SCN-004: Credential injection mechanism for Employment Spec secrets

# Hub — Task Management / Case Management:
    ## P2 (Medium):
        [ ] HUB-TSK-001: Case/task management integration — where case state lives in Hub
        [ ] HUB-TSK-002: Race condition handling for concurrent case updates
    ## P3 (Low):
        [ ] HUB-TSK-003: Team interdependence patterns (Pooled, Sequential, Reciprocal) — AOSM patterns


